section.forms

  h3 Forms

  h4 Default form

  form
    fieldset
      legend Regular form
      label Username
      input(type='text', placeholder='Insert your username', class='form-input')

      label Write a comment
      textarea.input This is a sample message

      button(type='submit', class='button button-primary') Send

  h4 Required inputs
  input(type='text', placeholder='This input is required', required, class='form-input')

  h4 Disabled inputs
  p  
    | To disable a form element add 
    code.inline-light disabled
    |  attribute.

  input(type='text', placeholder='This input is disabled', disabled, class='form-input')

  h4 Input validity
  p 
    | Sometimes you need to validate your forms. To have meaningful styling for valid and invalid inputs add 
    code.inline-light input-valid
    |  and 
    code.inline-light input-invalid
    |  classes respectively.

  input(type='text', value='@CNN', class='input-invalid', class='form-input')
  input(type='text', value='John Doe', class='input-valid', class='form-input')

  h4 Other form elements
  p
    | For radio and checkbox usage make sure to add 
    code.inline-light checkbox
    |  and 
    code.inline-light radio
    |  class to the label wrapping the actual input.

  form
    fieldset
      input(type='file', class='form-input')

      label.disabled.checkbox
        input(type='checkbox', disabled)
        | This is a disabled checkbox

      label.radio
        input(type='radio')
        | This is a radio button

      select
        option Option One

